      About this item

      • Matter-certified, Enhanced Compatibility: Easily controlled via voice command or mobile app with Amazon Alexa, Google Assistant, Apple HomeKit, and Samsung SmartThings. Supports 2.4GHz Wi-Fi only.
      • Exclusive Amazon Alexa Simple Setup: Select “Link to your Alexa” at checkout for the easiest setup experience. Then, just screw in the bulb, which will automatically connect to your Matter-compatible Alexa device.
      • Bright and Energy Efficient: 800 Lumens makes it brighter than many bulbs with the same wattage, but at only 9 watts, has a reduced environmental impact, saving up to 85% of energy usage without losing brightness or color quality.
      • HANDS-FREE VOICE OR APP CONTROL: Conveniently use voice commands or mobile app to easily control the lights, like adjusting brightness or colors, creating groups to control multiple lights at once, and routines to automate your schedules.
      • AWARD-WINNING INNOVATION: From Sengled, the smart lighting expert, we're the proud winner of 17 industry awards, including multiple CES Innovation Awards. As seen in major publications and backed by Sengled's 1,100 global patents and 2-year warranty.

      How customer reviews and ratings work

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      Customers say

      Customers find the smart light bulb easy to set up and appreciate its color options, with the ability to cycle through colors quickly and dim for movie nights. The bulb receives positive feedback for its quality and brightness, with one customer noting it can create tailored lighting experiences. However, connectivity issues are significant, with customers reporting constant disconnections from Wi-Fi. Functionality and compatibility with Alexa also receive mixed reviews, with some customers reporting it works well while others say it doesn't respond to commands. Value for money opinions are divided, with some finding it worth the price while others consider it not worth the cost.

      • WestInidianNative
        5.0 out of 5 stars Works Well, But Watch Your Network Settings!
        Reviewed in the United States on March 29, 2025
        Verified Purchase
        I was initially skeptical about this bulb, but it works. My only complaint is that if there is a power outage while the bulb is off, it does not remain off when the power returns. I experienced this when I was away for weeks on separate occasions and returned to find the light on.

        When I moved to a new apartment, I set up my Alexa without issues. The bulb initially connected but later showed as unresponsive in the app. I tried everything—moving it closer to the router, multiple resets—but nothing worked. I was about to toss it when I decided to check the reviews and discovered that the issue wasn't with the bulb but with my network settings.

        For this bulb to connect via Alexa, it must be on the same network as Alexa and use a 2.4 GHz Wi-Fi connection (not 5 GHz). Additionally, some routers have a feature that places wireless devices on a separate virtual network, which prevents proper communication. After disabling this feature, the bulb connected without any issues.

        In the end, the problem was not the bulb but my network configuration. I will be purchasing a few more.
